Package Spectrum

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    PeakComparator
    A general comparator of two peaks, note that in order to account for noise model in the scoring, this interface should implements compare method that accept null as argument and return an appropriate score accordingly for unexplained peaks
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ArraySpectrum
    Array implementation of a spectrum can be used for fast processing of spectrum instead of looping through a list of peak object in traditional spectrum (Note: only computing cosine is supported, add in other as needed)
    CandidateSpectrumGenerator
    Index spectrum library by precursor mass and store them in file only load part of the library into memory as a cache.
    Mass
    Mass information for amino acid and various type of ions
    Peak  
    PeakIntensityComparator
    A peak comparator based on intensity
    PeakMassComparator
    Comparator based on mass
    Peptide
    Represent a peptide
    PeptideMassAnalysis
    This class provide some general utility methods for analyze peptide masses
    Spectrum
    A data model for a mass spectrum
    SpectrumLib
    This class represent a spectral library, it contains two views on the spectral library, a Map view that index the spectra by its peptide and a List view that contains all the spectra
    SpectrumUtil
    Various utility method for spectrum
